text: Lina Sjöberg (born 6 September 1993) is a Swedish trampoline gymnast. She is a two-time gold medalist in the women's double mini event at the Trampoline Gymnastics World Championships. == Career == In 2017, she won the bronze medal in the women's double mini event at the 2017 World Games held in Wrocław, Poland. At the 2018 European Trampoline Championships held in Baku, Azerbaijan she won the bronze medal in the women's double mini event. In 2019, she represented Sweden at the 2019 European Games in the women's trampoline event.
